00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:02,900
[Sentimental Time 2AM's Beginning]

3
00:01:03,650 --> 00:01:06,950
2AM debuted on July 2008.

4
00:01:06,950 --> 00:01:10,300
4 numbers stand out for this group.

5
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:13,210
It's 2567.

6
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:22,610
Jo Kwon of 2AM was selected from the Nurture the Gifted Project.

7
00:01:22,610 --> 00:01:25,140
He is the owner of this number.

8
00:01:25,140 --> 00:01:31,130
I will try hard and practice to be a great artist. Thank you.

9
00:01:31,530 --> 00:01:33,670
[He's finally on stage today]

10
00:01:43,540 --> 00:01:52,050
[This debut song is a sentimental ballad that accumulated everything they practiced]

11
00:02:04,830 --> 00:02:09,560
[A sentimental ballad with subtle melody and sad lyrics]

12
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:15,200
[An ardent lyric that there is nothing to give but a song]

13
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:22,980
[Their debut song shined through their captivating voices]

14
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:17,930
2AM's Jo Kwon became a legend through his success of enduring 2,567 days as a trainee.

15
00:03:20,410 --> 00:03:23,530
- We're proud.
 - It's been 8 years?

16
00:03:23,530 --> 00:03:27,830
When I'm on variety or talk shows...

17
00:03:27,830 --> 00:03:32,020
People tell me to stop talking about my days as a trainee.

18
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:35,790
Many are sick of hearing it.

19
00:03:35,790 --> 00:03:40,960
There's no other choice since I spent my teens as a trainee...

20
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:46,250
- That's a third of your life.
 - That's all I have to say.

21
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:49,780
I have no memories of my school days.

22
00:03:50,260 --> 00:03:53,060
I had my first audition in the 6th grade.

23
00:03:53,060 --> 00:04:00,260
I never imagined it would take this long until I debuted.

24
00:04:00,260 --> 00:04:02,090
You waited 8 years.

25
00:04:02,090 --> 00:04:07,900
Now JYP tells you to get ready for your debut.

26
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:10,820
How did he tell you that?

27
00:04:10,820 --> 00:04:13,400
He sent me a text.

28
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:19,090
Today is the 2,567th day you were a trainee.

29
00:04:19,090 --> 00:04:25,450
He was a long-term JYP trainee that stayed the longest at 2,567 days.

30
00:04:25,450 --> 00:04:28,770
He finally got to stand on the stage he dreamed of.

31
00:04:46,090 --> 00:04:49,970
Jo Kwon silently overcame those 8 years.

32
00:04:49,970 --> 00:04:55,920
He led 2AM as the leader with 3 other members.

33
00:04:59,790 --> 00:05:04,560
Jo Kwon wasn't the only one who desperately wanted to be on stage.

34
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:10,350
They finished their first broadcast of their debut song "This Song" in tears.

35
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:12,750
They were moved to tears.

36
00:05:14,630 --> 00:05:18,420
What can they exchange this feeling for?

37
00:05:22,220 --> 00:05:26,260
The one who shed the most tears was Jo Kwon.

38
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:33,020
He can't believe this moment since he was a trainee for 8 long years.

39
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:37,500
This was the stage I dreamt and waited for until now.

40
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:44,080
Since I practiced under the burden and expectation of debuting.

41
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:50,050
Those 8 years seemed short when I was on stage.

42
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:53,930
I cried a lot because I was moved and felt proud.

43
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:04,600
"I have nothing to give but this song."

44
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:06,780
The voice and lyrics are sad.

45
00:06:06,780 --> 00:06:11,040
It's a special song that only 2AM can present.

46
00:06:32,470 --> 00:06:35,390
"This Song" is special as a collaborative stage.

47
00:06:35,390 --> 00:06:40,540
He performed with Sunye, a fellow JYP trainee.

48
00:06:40,540 --> 00:06:48,670
It must have been lovely to be in the spotlight with a friend.

49
00:06:50,820 --> 00:06:54,380
[Jo Kwon spent time as a trainee for a long time]

50
00:06:54,380 --> 00:06:58,180
[Sunye of Wonder Girls is a fellow labelmate and close friend]

51
00:06:58,180 --> 00:07:03,660
[He wanted to show his gratitude to her through this song]

52
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:46,210
This heart-filled song gained much interest as it was released.

53
00:07:46,210 --> 00:07:50,760
People paid attention to something else other than their song.

54
00:08:02,290 --> 00:08:07,020
[Their Own Keyword]

55
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:08,970
[Kkap]

56
00:08:08,970 --> 00:08:14,230
[A word describing Jo Kwon's one of a kind character]

57
00:08:15,650 --> 00:08:18,880
He left a strong impression at a surprise performance.

58
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:24,280
This is how his "kkap" character was born and left a mark in idol history.

59
00:08:28,150 --> 00:08:36,520
We did a special called "Wonder Boys" on Inkigayo's 500th episode.

60
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:39,890
There was a Jo Kwon crisis.

61
00:08:39,890 --> 00:08:41,120
On the internet?

62
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:45,400
Many fans said that was the day "Kkap Kwon" was born.

63
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:53,610
There's this part in one of Wonder Girls' songs.

64
00:08:53,610 --> 00:08:58,320
I expressed those emotions well.

65
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,940
[He sure is Kkap Kwon]

66
00:09:05,940 --> 00:09:12,330
[Wonder Girls parody during Inkigayo's 500th special]

67
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,980
[This is how Kkap Kwon was born]

68
00:09:15,980 --> 00:09:21,930
Only that part was made into an animated GIF and spread online.

69
00:09:21,930 --> 00:09:24,910
JYP called me right away.

70
00:09:24,910 --> 00:09:28,890
"Kwon, stop doing that."

71
00:09:28,890 --> 00:09:33,240
"You shouldn't do that since you're a ballad singer."

72
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:37,470
The other members told me, "How can we sing ballads now because of you?"

73
00:09:37,470 --> 00:09:45,300
You know Jo Kwon's Kkap Kwon dances on various programs...

74
00:09:52,570 --> 00:09:57,780
I happened to watch that on television and was surprised.

75
00:09:57,780 --> 00:10:03,090
There's an image when I create a group. The four of them are singing like this.

76
00:10:03,090 --> 00:10:06,110
But he's doing such a dance with such expressions.

77
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:08,820
He didn't just dance but his expressions were...

78
00:10:08,820 --> 00:10:10,700
I was really surprised and called him.

79
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:14,360
I scolded him, "What are you doing? You're a ballad singer."

80
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:17,200
- You did?
 - Yes.

81
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:21,480
He didn't do it in one program but started doing it again.

82
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:27,220
Jo Kwon's instinct "kkap" goes against JYP's dislikes.

83
00:10:27,220 --> 00:10:30,840
Didn't you sense anything when you casted him?

84
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,930
Not at all because he was in elementary school.

85
00:10:32,930 --> 00:10:40,170
He was unique at the audition and did Lee Jung-hyun's "Come On."

86
00:10:40,170 --> 00:10:42,660
But he went more crazy than the original artist.

87
00:10:55,180 --> 00:11:01,190
We agreed that he can do such dances but behave himself inbetween.

88
00:11:01,190 --> 00:11:01,820
Inbetween?

89
00:11:01,820 --> 00:11:06,360
To be cautious inbetween when he does such dances.

90
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:11,260
We get hooked the more we see it. I guess JYP has given up on it.

91
00:11:12,110 --> 00:11:14,120
[Jo Kwon is rising as a agitating woman!]

92
00:11:15,940 --> 00:11:17,270
[Is my mascara okay?]

93
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,500
[What do we do with them...]

94
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:29,510
Kkap Kwon comes out anywhere. How can he not stand out?

95
00:11:30,660 --> 00:11:32,160
[If you're going to shake, you should shake like this]

96
00:11:36,210 --> 00:11:37,250
[My son's the best!]

97
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:40,640
He even made his own "Kkap" awards.

98
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,550
You prepared them?

99
00:11:43,710 --> 00:11:45,580
[Kkap Kwon Best 3 Wonder Kkap Kwon!]

100
00:11:46,150 --> 00:11:49,480
- It's this picture.
 - When was that?

101
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:53,580
We parodied the Wonder Girls as Wonder Boys once.

102
00:11:53,580 --> 00:11:56,960
I made this expression and this was the screen capture.

103
00:11:56,960 --> 00:12:02,700
This is beyond "kkap" and close to horror.

104
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,490
Can you make that face?

105
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:05,370
[Red sun!]

106
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:12,810
[Kkap Kwon Best 2 Director Jo!]

107
00:12:13,460 --> 00:12:19,180
JYP artists had a poster shoot for the year-end concert.

108
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:23,010
JYP was supposed to be here.

109
00:12:23,010 --> 00:12:26,630
But I'm here and he's there.

110
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:30,740
JYP was hard on me at first.

111
00:12:30,740 --> 00:12:35,490
"Why are you trying to be funny? You're a ballad singer."

112
00:12:35,490 --> 00:12:39,850
He said a lot of things and I was scolded.

113
00:12:39,850 --> 00:12:43,170
But now he goes around saying good things about me.

114
00:12:43,170 --> 00:12:44,950
How did he change?

115
00:12:44,950 --> 00:12:49,770
I'm known as Director Jo at the agency now.

116
00:12:49,770 --> 00:12:53,080
Can you do a similar pose if a picture is taken now?

117
00:12:58,970 --> 00:13:01,670
Another pose. One, two, three!

118
00:13:01,670 --> 00:13:03,890
[His "kkap" instincts]

119
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:07,700
Let's stop.

120
00:13:09,410 --> 00:13:11,790
The last is...

121
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:14,360
[Kkap Best 1]

122
00:13:15,340 --> 00:13:19,530
We parodied Brown Eyed Girls as Dirty Eyed Girls...

123
00:13:19,530 --> 00:13:22,060
This was during the filming of our music video.

124
00:13:22,060 --> 00:13:26,320
I look similar to a character in a well-known Japanese comic.

125
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:27,900
- It's the same.
 - It really is.

126
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:31,050
- It does look the same.
 - It is similar.

127
00:13:31,550 --> 00:13:37,400
I'll make a prediction. It's been a year since he rose as "Kkap Kwon."

128
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:41,240
This will last about 5 years.

129
00:13:41,740 --> 00:13:44,080
What is your secret?

130
00:13:46,650 --> 00:13:49,540
- I'll do a cam version.
 - Alright. Make it cute.

131
00:13:52,980 --> 00:13:54,510
That's a nice pose.

132
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:56,670
That's Jo Kwon for you.

133
00:13:56,670 --> 00:14:03,540
He became big with "kkap." How did he hold this in for 2,567 days?

134
00:14:03,540 --> 00:14:07,460
Let's wait and see this one of a kind character.

135
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,580
Now...

136
00:14:11,580 --> 00:14:17,050
It's Go Hyun-jung and Jo Kwon's age.

137
00:14:17,620 --> 00:14:19,530
[Ex-soldier idol]

138
00:14:19,530 --> 00:14:26,550
[A male idol who finished his mandatory military service]

139
00:14:26,940 --> 00:14:29,990
We can't leave out Changmin's voice from 2AM.

140
00:14:29,990 --> 00:14:34,910
He drew attention not only with his excellent voice but also his nickname.

141
00:14:34,910 --> 00:14:38,600
It's ex-soldier idol, an idol who finished his military service.

142
00:14:45,510 --> 00:14:54,730
During the early days of my debut, I was known as ex-soldier idol.

143
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:58,820
You know those that completed their military service.

144
00:14:58,820 --> 00:15:03,760
I qualified for the police marching band.

145
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:08,760
During my military service, MBC came to film.

146
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:14,620
I had a bad case of the flu and was sleeping upstairs.

147
00:15:14,620 --> 00:15:19,090
I was resting when the commander came in.

148
00:15:19,090 --> 00:15:21,940
"Changmin, I think you should go down and sing."

149
00:15:21,940 --> 00:15:24,360
When I said I needed to rest...

150
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:28,050
He said, "Do you want a special leave?"

151
00:15:28,050 --> 00:15:31,780
So... I did it.

152
00:15:31,780 --> 00:15:34,710
[Vacations can make even sick soldiers to get up right away!]

153
00:15:34,860 --> 00:15:39,860
Do all of you want to see Changmin singing at that time?

154
00:15:39,860 --> 00:15:41,170
Yes!

155
00:15:41,170 --> 00:15:42,580
This is being revealed for the first time.

156
00:15:42,580 --> 00:15:45,080
- This is really...
 - I'm getting curious.

157
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:48,130
Let's watch the clip.

158
00:15:49,220 --> 00:15:53,250
Next is a music project that will please your ears.

159
00:15:53,620 --> 00:15:57,110
The Police Symphony Orchestra in Yongin, Gyeonggi-do.

160
00:15:57,110 --> 00:16:00,610
[This is the barrack Changmin used!]

161
00:16:01,630 --> 00:16:04,000
[Where is he?]

162
00:16:13,820 --> 00:16:18,270
[He fights against the flu with a red face to get a leave]

163
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:24,400
[Showing skills with a bug spray]

164
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:28,980
He shows off his showmanship by using the right props.

165
00:16:28,980 --> 00:16:32,140
His talents were exceptional since his time in the military.

166
00:16:32,140 --> 00:16:34,380
I was asked to go to an audition.

167
00:16:34,380 --> 00:16:41,940
It was a JYP audition and I said I'll go since I like JYP's songs.

168
00:16:41,940 --> 00:16:46,770
I went to the audition but I didn't get news of the results.

169
00:16:46,770 --> 00:16:50,580
I was discharged from the military without knowing the audition results.

170
00:16:50,580 --> 00:16:56,850
I hung out with my friends all night and received a call the next day.

171
00:16:56,850 --> 00:17:00,750
I received a call saying, "Come to JYPE and sign the contract."

172
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:08,600
The day after my discharge, I went to JYPE and...

173
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:12,990
He went to the audition during his leave and signed the contract after discharge.

174
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:16,210
How he became a singer is also extraordinary.

175
00:17:16,210 --> 00:17:21,720
He was also active in the group Homme with Lee Hyun of 8Eight.

176
00:17:47,550 --> 00:17:50,300
What made you to be in a group together.

177
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:56,700
I put this song aside because there were some heavy parts for me to sing alone.

178
00:17:56,700 --> 00:18:01,370
I was suggested to sing with Changmin and I thought that would be great.

179
00:18:01,370 --> 00:18:04,940
But how he entered this group was different.

180
00:18:04,940 --> 00:18:08,130
He heard the song first...

181
00:18:08,130 --> 00:18:11,000
You're younger than him?

182
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,490
Yes, I'm 3 years younger.

183
00:18:14,410 --> 00:18:17,580
What is this feeling?

184
00:18:17,580 --> 00:18:22,180
I didn't say anything but I think we're thinking the same thing.

185
00:18:22,180 --> 00:18:27,330
Changmin is younger than Lee Hyun who is currently in the military.

186
00:18:27,330 --> 00:18:31,020
Don't be upset. I wasn't surprised.

187
00:18:31,020 --> 00:18:37,670
He stood out since there weren't many ex-soldier idols at the time.

188
00:18:37,670 --> 00:18:40,390
Good thing you served early on.

189
00:18:40,390 --> 00:18:42,440
This is a bonus.

190
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:48,370
Including myself, we made a military version of this song.

191
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:53,960
[Disciplined moves!]

192
00:18:55,950 --> 00:18:58,420
[A resounding voice!]

193
00:18:58,420 --> 00:19:01,040
[They prepared a military version of a girl group's song!]

194
00:19:03,750 --> 00:19:07,000
What's the MND's time?

195
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:10,730
[Tick tock, tick tock the time just flies]

196
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:15,680
[Radiating masculine appeal]

197
00:19:20,860 --> 00:19:23,280
Hey, mister! What's your name?

198
00:19:23,280 --> 00:19:26,400
Public service worker Kim Dong-wan!

199
00:19:26,730 --> 00:19:30,640
He's a public service worker? Are you by any chance also...

200
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:33,170
- I'm not Pyo In-bong!
 - I see you're not.

201
00:19:40,620 --> 00:19:42,460
[1, 2, 3, 4! 1, 2, 3, 4!]

202
00:19:45,260 --> 00:19:49,940
I was sleeping in the dorm and Seulong said we got a new member.

203
00:19:49,940 --> 00:19:54,780
- I ran in with the notebook.
 - But he was laughing.

204
00:19:54,780 --> 00:19:56,770
His picture was posted!

205
00:19:56,770 --> 00:19:59,070
It was a clip of him during the audition.

206
00:19:59,070 --> 00:20:04,350
"We got a new member but I'm at a loss for words."

207
00:20:04,350 --> 00:20:05,810
What's the reason?

208
00:20:05,810 --> 00:20:13,310
I got up from bed and the two of us didn't say anything for 5 minutes.

209
00:20:13,310 --> 00:20:16,600
"Is he a vocal trainer?"

210
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:22,600
His looks made us think that he'll sing well.

211
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:24,440
I mean, he is an idol.

212
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:28,470
We thought he would be skilled because he did sing well.

213
00:20:28,470 --> 00:20:34,330
That's what we thought. He had spots on his face and was just discharged.

214
00:20:34,330 --> 00:20:36,930
So he wouldn't have been picked if it wasn't for his singing?

215
00:20:36,930 --> 00:20:42,510
Lookism needs to be eradicated from Korea.

216
00:20:42,890 --> 00:20:44,770
What's your wish?

217
00:20:44,770 --> 00:20:47,050
I want my mouth to go in!

218
00:20:47,050 --> 00:20:50,190
Just live as you are.

219
00:20:50,190 --> 00:20:57,410
He's at ease for being discharged but feels uncomfortable of his looks.

220
00:20:57,410 --> 00:20:59,680
I thought he took my advice...

221
00:21:00,750 --> 00:21:05,730
But recently his skills and looks were upgraded.

222
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:16,790
You were recognized for your singing in the group 2AM.

223
00:21:16,790 --> 00:21:19,230
Is there something else you want to be known for?

224
00:21:19,230 --> 00:21:21,320
- Be honest?
 - Yes.

225
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:23,460
[Deep in thought]

226
00:21:23,460 --> 00:21:27,430
For my looks...

227
00:21:27,430 --> 00:21:32,490
He wants to be known for his looks. Guess he was a bright character.

228
00:21:32,490 --> 00:21:36,670
I wonder what it feels like for people to say you look good.

229
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:38,720
You guys hear that.

230
00:21:51,390 --> 00:21:55,970
[2AM's Music]

231
00:21:56,560 --> 00:22:02,570
2AM drew attention with various activities along with their popular debut song.

232
00:22:02,570 --> 00:22:06,940
They released their 2nd single in 2009 after their debut.

233
00:22:06,940 --> 00:22:15,060
They presented their own ballad with "Confession of a Friend."

234
00:22:22,020 --> 00:22:26,540
[A beautiful harmony stands out with powerful singing and masculine appeal]

235
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:46,390
[A ballad containing the regret of not becoming lovers from being friends]

236
00:22:46,390 --> 00:22:56,620
[They're more stronger and masculine since their debut and their harmony stands out]

237
00:25:45,780 --> 00:25:54,140
In 2010, their special ballad potential was unleashed in their 1st mini-album.

238
00:25:54,140 --> 00:25:58,540
"Even If I Die I Can't Let You Go" was made by producer Bang Si-hyuk.

239
00:26:16,320 --> 00:26:19,460
[This song was born from the meeting of 2AM and producer Bang Si-hyuk]

240
00:26:19,460 --> 00:26:24,090
[It's a hybrid ballad with refined sounds and sentimental vocals]

241
00:26:24,090 --> 00:26:26,770
[To keep the balance between the concept of ballads and idols...]

242
00:26:26,770 --> 00:26:30,380
[Electronic sounds were used in this ballad]

243
00:26:30,380 --> 00:26:37,450
[The static-like sound in the chorus is unique and made with a synthesizer]

244
00:26:37,450 --> 00:26:40,470
[It was intentionally given such a sound]

245
00:26:40,470 --> 00:26:43,450
[It topped various music charts with its release]

246
00:26:43,450 --> 00:26:46,480
[Not only did they take first on broadcast...]

247
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:50,670
[They received the grand prize at the year-end awards]

248
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:16,790
- How do you feel?
 - Yes, how do you feel?

249
00:27:18,230 --> 00:27:23,040
First of all, I would like to thank my dad and our manager.

250
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:28,450
I thank JYP who's in the US right now and Young-kwon.

251
00:27:28,450 --> 00:27:31,610
We also thank Mr. Yang.

252
00:27:31,610 --> 00:27:37,300
Kwon is crying right now... Hey, say something.

253
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:50,220
Thank you. I thank God, my parents...

254
00:27:54,130 --> 00:27:59,760
Thank you everyone. We'll do our best.

255
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:02,560
I love you mom and dad! Thank you God!

256
00:28:05,500 --> 00:28:09,650
Not only did they get their first trophy with this song...

257
00:28:09,650 --> 00:28:14,990
But they also received the grand prize at the 2010 Golden Disk Awards.

258
00:28:14,990 --> 00:28:19,150
They reached the top they dreamed of with their own ballads.

259
00:28:37,660 --> 00:28:43,060
They released their first full-length album in the second half of 2010.

260
00:28:43,060 --> 00:28:48,930
They released double title tracks and showed strong as the best group in ballads.

261
00:28:57,420 --> 00:29:02,620
[A ballad describing the pain and loneliness of breaking up]

262
00:29:21,130 --> 00:29:24,090
[This song describes the pain and loneliness of breaking up]

263
00:29:24,090 --> 00:29:27,130
[Their ardent sentiments on top of the lonely accompaniment stand out]

264
00:29:27,130 --> 00:29:29,390
[When "Even If I Die I Can't Let You Go" was released, they worked on this song]

265
00:29:29,390 --> 00:29:33,120
[It was decided a long time ago to be the title track of their 1st full-length album]

266
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:39,120
[Their looks also matured with suits that went with the song]

267
00:30:53,460 --> 00:30:58,450
[The unique melody that's strongly attractive went with their voices]

268
00:30:58,450 --> 00:31:00,820
[Due to the song's appeal...]

269
00:31:00,820 --> 00:31:05,890
[Producer Bang Si-hyuk gave much thought on the title track and decided to go double]

270
00:31:05,890 --> 00:31:10,880
[Before its release, a teaser of the members shedding tears attracted attention]

271
00:32:03,980 --> 00:32:07,890
They didn't sing only quiet ballads.

272
00:32:07,890 --> 00:32:11,290
They've also transformed with fast tempo songs.

273
00:32:20,940 --> 00:32:23,980
[A dance song with a bright and catchy melody]

274
00:32:23,980 --> 00:32:26,990
[It's completely different from the sad image of their debut song]

275
00:32:26,990 --> 00:32:30,010
[They're lively and dance cute moves in this second single]

276
00:32:30,010 --> 00:32:33,050
[A clip of this song performed at an awards ceremony was revealed]

277
00:32:33,050 --> 00:32:36,970
[The fans' request and overwhelming support made this their 2nd single]

278
00:32:40,620 --> 00:32:49,080
Their most shocking performance was when they danced in "I Was Wrong."

279
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:53,100
Their moves changed a lot in the past two years.

280
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:19,750
[A dance song with intense string melody, piano, and Eurobeat drum sounds in the intro]

281
00:33:19,750 --> 00:33:22,610
[They wanted to present a sentiment that goes beyond a ballad]

282
00:33:22,610 --> 00:33:25,610
[Their attempt on acting in the song's music drama also drew attention]

283
00:35:46,830 --> 00:35:52,740
Before you see the dance, you need to compare our expressions.

284
00:35:52,740 --> 00:35:55,580
The biggest change is our expressions in the song.

285
00:35:55,580 --> 00:35:58,000
That freshness from our 1st album.

286
00:35:58,000 --> 00:35:59,870
I'll go down and watch.

287
00:36:23,240 --> 00:36:26,340
Let's see "I Was Wrong."

288
00:36:38,670 --> 00:36:42,130
Expression is as important as the moves.

289
00:36:42,130 --> 00:36:44,700
But be careful of getting screen captured.

290
00:36:44,700 --> 00:36:47,280
We can't do anything about the ones that were already done.

291
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:50,920
We can't leave out the powerful Kkap Kwon dance for this song.

292
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:54,000
We'll excuse ourselves and become his shadow.

293
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:01,420
[Shadow]

294
00:37:11,490 --> 00:37:13,240
Thank you.

295
00:37:13,240 --> 00:37:18,990
It seemed we were successful in our image makeover but Jo Kwon...

296
00:37:18,990 --> 00:37:25,170
We're curious of their special stage since they can sing various genres.

297
00:37:35,550 --> 00:37:42,780
Let's find out more about their charms when they're together and alone.

298
00:37:54,560 --> 00:38:03,530
[Ranking! 2AM's Special Stage]

299
00:38:08,850 --> 00:38:13,540
2AM sings "Sunday Morning," a sweet pop song.

300
00:39:20,870 --> 00:39:25,450
Seulong and IU's sweet harmony where they nagged each other.

301
00:40:30,220 --> 00:40:35,700
"Woman of the Beach," an exciting song for summer sung by 2AM.

302
00:41:57,400 --> 00:42:01,730
Another harmony on top of perfect harmony! A collaborative stage with Sweet Sorrow.

303
00:43:48,310 --> 00:43:56,330
They can even sing JYP's songs well. Their version of g.o.d's song is No.1.

304
00:46:02,270 --> 00:46:03,530
Clap your hands!

305
00:46:05,710 --> 00:46:07,600
Sing along if you know it!

306
00:47:46,720 --> 00:47:55,420
[What Do We Do? 2AM's Confession]

307
00:47:55,730 --> 00:47:59,720
Seulong appeared on this show on August 3, 2010.

308
00:47:59,720 --> 00:48:05,720
He said his ideal woman and only love is Shin Mina.

309
00:48:05,720 --> 00:48:14,680
On a happy Christmas in 2011, where and what did you do?

310
00:48:15,560 --> 00:48:18,790
December 25, 2011.

311
00:48:18,790 --> 00:48:20,610
- We had a concert.
 - A concert?

312
00:48:20,610 --> 00:48:23,730
What did you do afterwards?

313
00:48:23,730 --> 00:48:25,260
- We had a get-together.
 - Where?

314
00:48:25,260 --> 00:48:27,940
At a restaurant serving pork belly.

315
00:48:31,160 --> 00:48:33,940
[What is that?]

316
00:48:33,940 --> 00:48:36,740
What else do you want if you eat pork belly?

317
00:48:36,740 --> 00:48:38,690
- Noodles.
 - That's right.

318
00:48:38,690 --> 00:48:40,380
In detail...

319
00:48:40,380 --> 00:48:43,220
You want noodles if you eat pork belly?

320
00:48:43,220 --> 00:48:44,240
There's a reason.

321
00:48:44,240 --> 00:48:46,940
Boom? You always eat noodles after eating pork belly, right?

322
00:48:46,940 --> 00:48:47,710
I do.

323
00:48:47,710 --> 00:48:51,190
- And what noodles?
 - Rice noodles.

324
00:48:51,190 --> 00:48:56,960
You were with someone at a rice noodle restaurant around 3 AM.

325
00:48:56,960 --> 00:49:00,000
And a lot of people know because of the articles.

326
00:49:00,000 --> 00:49:05,140
Instead of denying it, it's now time for you to be honest.

327
00:49:05,140 --> 00:49:10,870
Who did you meet at that restaurant at 3 AM?

328
00:49:10,870 --> 00:49:13,530
It was Sohee, my labelmate.

329
00:49:13,530 --> 00:49:15,780
[The one with Seulong was Wonder Girls' Sohee!]

330
00:49:15,780 --> 00:49:17,100
- Park Ji-yoon?
 - Yes?

331
00:49:17,100 --> 00:49:24,210
If you meet someone at 3 AM... it's not 2 or 4 but 3 AM...

332
00:49:24,210 --> 00:49:27,050
According to experience, what feelings might you have to meet at that time?

333
00:49:27,050 --> 00:49:29,100
You have to like that person.

334
00:49:30,820 --> 00:49:35,170
I heard that the birth of mankind is at 3 AM.

335
00:49:35,170 --> 00:49:37,840
[What?]

336
00:49:37,840 --> 00:49:40,260
[What's with that?]

337
00:49:42,710 --> 00:49:45,760
[Boom was taken aback]

338
00:49:46,910 --> 00:49:52,340
You're close with Sohee but that picture spread dating rumors.

339
00:49:52,340 --> 00:49:58,880
It could have developed into a relationship or it did not.

340
00:49:58,880 --> 00:50:00,650
What happened?

341
00:50:00,650 --> 00:50:03,680
Nothing... happened.

342
00:50:03,680 --> 00:50:05,190
Don't stutter.

343
00:50:05,190 --> 00:50:08,030
Sohee was the one in Seulong's dating rumors.

344
00:50:08,030 --> 00:50:11,090
But there's someone else that Seulong likes.

345
00:50:11,090 --> 00:50:12,900
It's Shin Mina.

346
00:50:14,540 --> 00:50:17,130
He has her ID picture.

347
00:50:17,130 --> 00:50:18,650
[It's not like he'll get documents in her place...]

348
00:50:18,650 --> 00:50:22,100
You're afraid of this one person in Korea?

349
00:50:22,100 --> 00:50:23,380
Who is that?

350
00:50:23,380 --> 00:50:28,470
That is Shin Mina.

351
00:50:28,470 --> 00:50:31,080
[He fears her the most?]

352
00:50:31,080 --> 00:50:33,100
You're afraid of her?

353
00:50:33,100 --> 00:50:35,960
I get nervous.

354
00:50:37,660 --> 00:50:48,490
It's been made public a few times that his ideal woman is Shin Mina.

355
00:50:48,490 --> 00:50:49,860
Does your family know?

356
00:50:49,860 --> 00:50:51,100
[She had heard about it]

357
00:50:55,430 --> 00:50:57,690
[He can't look at her because his heart feels like exploding]

358
00:50:57,690 --> 00:50:59,300
[This beast idol falls before love!]

359
00:51:01,220 --> 00:51:05,300
Idols' ideal types are... Kyu-jong likes Oh Se-jung...

360
00:51:05,300 --> 00:51:11,650
It's really big news that Seulong likes Shin Mina.

361
00:51:11,650 --> 00:51:16,740
This is an unexpected competitor.

362
00:51:16,740 --> 00:51:20,360
I beg you to not turn around.

363
00:51:22,490 --> 00:51:23,730
Really?

364
00:51:23,730 --> 00:51:27,480
I get the goosebumps all over my body.

365
00:51:27,480 --> 00:51:29,460
What happens if she turns around?

366
00:51:32,720 --> 00:51:33,770
[Eyes are tightly shut]

367
00:51:35,520 --> 00:51:37,850
[Please... don't look...]

368
00:51:40,090 --> 00:51:42,070
[Bashful nine-tailed fox]

369
00:51:46,200 --> 00:51:49,040
[Singing "Nothing Better" for her]

370
00:51:50,070 --> 00:51:51,450
[I'm nervous]

371
00:51:53,880 --> 00:51:55,360
[Don't be nervous...]

372
00:52:00,120 --> 00:52:04,700
[He was her fan for 10 years]

373
00:52:04,700 --> 00:52:08,150
[He's actually singing before her...]

374
00:52:11,820 --> 00:52:15,400
[He's so nervous he can't even look at her...]

375
00:52:19,690 --> 00:52:22,910
[Seems like everyone's jealous]

376
00:52:37,100 --> 00:52:41,620
[His dream was to be on television with her someday]

377
00:52:47,140 --> 00:52:50,010
[Should I look or not?]

378
00:52:52,060 --> 00:52:55,560
[He doesn't have the courage to look at her yet...]

379
00:52:55,560 --> 00:52:57,100
Look at her at least once!

380
00:52:59,200 --> 00:53:02,150
[He finally looked at her!]

381
00:53:03,050 --> 00:53:05,400
[A dreamlike second...]

382
00:53:08,290 --> 00:53:10,660
[His dream came true!]

383
00:53:17,140 --> 00:53:20,800
[A pure heart of a fan who liked her for 10 years...]

384
00:53:30,130 --> 00:53:31,530
That's it.

385
00:53:32,790 --> 00:53:35,550
[A song of love that stirs the heart...]

386
00:53:36,810 --> 00:53:40,160
We acknowledge his love for her.

387
00:53:40,160 --> 00:53:42,480
Jinwoon also made a sudden confession.

388
00:53:42,480 --> 00:53:44,250
Can you tell us who you like?

389
00:53:44,250 --> 00:53:45,250
Of course.

390
00:53:47,350 --> 00:53:49,740
It's Seohyun.

391
00:53:49,740 --> 00:53:51,280
- Seohyun?
 - Yes.

392
00:53:51,280 --> 00:53:53,760
- Isn't she cute?
 - I get nervous.

393
00:53:54,710 --> 00:53:59,230
We met in the hall and I turned and ran away because I'm her fan.

394
00:53:59,230 --> 00:54:00,270
- Really?
 - Yes.

395
00:54:00,270 --> 00:54:01,920
You're so innocent.

396
00:54:01,920 --> 00:54:03,570
That's right!

397
00:54:03,570 --> 00:54:06,500
My friend... Seohyun of Girls' Generation...

398
00:54:06,500 --> 00:54:07,340
Something to eat?

399
00:54:07,340 --> 00:54:08,740
Seohyun of Girls' Generation?

400
00:54:08,740 --> 00:54:11,680
She asked to eat together before I left so we had breakfast.

401
00:54:11,680 --> 00:54:14,620
She gave me vitamins after breakfast.

402
00:54:14,620 --> 00:54:17,300
[She gave him vitamins as a gift?]

403
00:54:18,330 --> 00:54:20,500
She gave me these.

404
00:54:20,500 --> 00:54:23,600
[That's a letter by Seohyun!]

405
00:54:23,600 --> 00:54:25,660
Seohyun of Girls' Generation?

406
00:54:25,660 --> 00:54:31,950
Vitamins from Seohyun? That itself is vitamin.

407
00:54:31,950 --> 00:54:36,600
But he has another room in his heart and that's for Lee Min-jung.

408
00:54:36,600 --> 00:54:41,010
I really like Lee Min-jung.

409
00:54:41,010 --> 00:54:44,160
- Lee Min-jung?
 - I really like her.

410
00:54:44,160 --> 00:54:46,930
You know the contact lens commercial she's in?

411
00:54:46,930 --> 00:54:52,700
"Giving up for health." It drives me nuts. Her eyes are so pretty.

412
00:54:52,700 --> 00:54:59,780
He wants poor vision just to put on those contacts.

413
00:55:00,400 --> 00:55:03,060
Even when you see the ad poster?

414
00:55:03,060 --> 00:55:10,490
I love it, but she came to our concert.

415
00:55:10,490 --> 00:55:11,440
How?

416
00:55:11,440 --> 00:55:16,410
We got acquainted after appearing in a one-act drama together.

417
00:55:16,410 --> 00:55:19,720
I invited her and she was in the waiting room.

418
00:55:19,720 --> 00:55:23,490
That's when he got really nervous.

419
00:55:23,490 --> 00:55:27,190
I wanted to take a picture with her since she was there.

420
00:55:27,190 --> 00:55:32,040
I was pacing up and down to get a picture taken...

421
00:55:32,040 --> 00:55:35,450
But I couldn't ask her to take a picture with her.

422
00:55:35,450 --> 00:55:38,240
I was so nervous that I hid in the dressing room.

423
00:55:38,240 --> 00:55:41,780
I didn't do anything wrong but I was trembling as I hid.

424
00:55:41,780 --> 00:55:45,430
I thought, "I should act like a man, greet her and get a picture taken."

425
00:55:45,430 --> 00:55:50,240
But we could see him because he's tall.

426
00:55:50,750 --> 00:55:52,150
That's even stranger.

427
00:55:52,150 --> 00:55:55,110
Didn't Lee Seung-gi shoot many commercials with Lee Min-jung?

428
00:55:55,110 --> 00:55:57,100
I took many pictures with her.

429
00:55:58,030 --> 00:55:59,810
[I'm friends with her]

430
00:56:00,470 --> 00:56:02,030
Jealous?

431
00:56:02,030 --> 00:56:03,310
[Really jealous]

432
00:56:07,330 --> 00:56:10,010
- I could make arrangements.
 - You can do that?

433
00:56:11,300 --> 00:56:14,840
I got acquainted with her and I meet her on the set so...

434
00:56:14,840 --> 00:56:17,830
- It's okay.
 - Why?

435
00:56:18,660 --> 00:56:21,810
[He's holding on to his pride...]

436
00:56:21,810 --> 00:56:25,700
Is Lee Min-jung the only one for you? Wasn't Kang So-ra...

437
00:56:25,700 --> 00:56:28,870
He's currently shooting a drama with her.

438
00:56:28,870 --> 00:56:29,910
Yes I am.

439
00:56:29,910 --> 00:56:32,260
Leeteuk has a long face.

440
00:56:32,940 --> 00:56:34,440
[Leeteuk and Kang So-ra are newlyweds]

441
00:56:34,440 --> 00:56:37,360
Didn't you get a divorce?

442
00:56:37,360 --> 00:56:39,420
The station is on a strike.

443
00:56:43,110 --> 00:56:46,010
[They've been separated...]

444
00:56:46,010 --> 00:56:48,500
[They want to see each other but can't]

445
00:56:48,810 --> 00:56:51,400
You can't meet during a strike.

446
00:56:51,400 --> 00:56:54,080
[Let us love each other again]

447
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:57,120
[That cracks us up]

448
00:56:57,940 --> 00:57:01,320
It's a strike. We didn't break off our engagement.

449
00:57:01,320 --> 00:57:04,870
Would you pick Kang So-ra over Lee Min-jung?

450
00:57:04,870 --> 00:57:06,340
You're going on a trip.

451
00:57:06,340 --> 00:57:07,780
- A trip.
 - A trip?

452
00:57:07,780 --> 00:57:10,670
- Planned?
 - On impulse.

453
00:57:10,670 --> 00:57:13,240
You pick them up in front of their house.

454
00:57:13,240 --> 00:57:16,190
- Whose house is it?
 - He's into it.

455
00:57:16,190 --> 00:57:19,820
He just gets into it whatever it is.

456
00:57:19,820 --> 00:57:22,710
The trunk is filled with food and you depart.

457
00:57:22,710 --> 00:57:24,080
- Is there a mat?
 - Of course.

458
00:57:24,080 --> 00:57:25,720
- You call, "Come out."
 - Come out?

459
00:57:25,720 --> 00:57:27,430
Who steps out of the door?

460
00:57:27,430 --> 00:57:30,190
- Whose house is it?
 - Who is it?

461
00:57:30,190 --> 00:57:32,170
I choose Lee Min-jung.

462
00:57:32,170 --> 00:57:33,300
[Me?]

463
00:57:33,300 --> 00:57:36,030
- I'll be straightforward.
 - Alright, shoot it.

464
00:57:36,030 --> 00:57:37,380
Are you close with Lee Min-jung?

465
00:57:37,380 --> 00:57:39,510
- You like her, right?
 - I'm jealous.

466
00:57:39,510 --> 00:57:41,670
You should create an occasion for him if you know that.

467
00:57:41,670 --> 00:57:42,690
I'm jealous.

468
00:57:42,690 --> 00:57:50,230
I did during the concert but it was Jo Kwon who took pictures.

469
00:57:50,230 --> 00:57:53,340
And Jinwoon was hiding in the dressing room.

470
00:57:53,340 --> 00:57:54,380
I was embarassed.

471
00:57:54,380 --> 00:57:58,600
Jinwoon was shy even though the members made an effort.

472
00:57:58,600 --> 00:58:00,240
Does she know?

473
00:58:00,240 --> 00:58:01,710
Yes, she does.

474
00:58:01,710 --> 00:58:04,760
We acknowledge that he likes Lee Min-jung.

475
00:58:04,760 --> 00:58:08,580
Let's listen to their hypothetical proposal song.

476
00:58:08,580 --> 00:58:13,470
We always make idols do a hypothetical proposal.

477
00:58:14,180 --> 00:58:19,500
Since I'm the youngest, I'll make it cute.

478
00:58:21,370 --> 00:58:28,970
I'll always make this pretty smile if you'll go out with me. I'm sorry.

479
00:58:32,710 --> 00:58:35,890
No, it was cute.

480
00:58:35,890 --> 00:58:38,320
Can we change to a three member group?

481
00:58:40,160 --> 00:58:41,390
Next?

482
00:58:41,390 --> 00:58:46,380
I'll do a short song with some aegyo.

483
00:58:46,380 --> 00:58:49,850
- Then go to the front...
 - But I can't do it alone.

484
00:58:49,850 --> 00:58:51,580
The members have to help.

485
00:58:51,580 --> 00:58:55,630
- Are you going to do that?
 - We play around like this.

486
00:59:16,680 --> 00:59:22,840
I'll sing after speaking in a Busan dialect.

487
00:59:22,840 --> 00:59:24,000
Fine.

488
00:59:24,940 --> 00:59:27,830
Jung-eun?

489
00:59:27,830 --> 00:59:32,130
- I have something to say.
 - What is it?

490
00:59:32,130 --> 00:59:33,900
Please have my child.

491
01:00:05,300 --> 01:00:09,290
I would've regretted it if 2AM didn't do this.

492
01:00:24,350 --> 01:00:32,270
[They Shine Alone and Together]

493
01:00:32,860 --> 01:00:36,980
They are all exceptional singers and do well on their own as well.

494
01:00:36,980 --> 01:00:40,140
They each went solo and had their own projects.

495
01:00:42,970 --> 01:00:51,280
[Seulong]

