01:00:51,580 --> 01:00:55,330
Seulong went on stage first not as 2AM but as a duet.

497
01:00:55,330 --> 01:00:59,250
He did a surprise colloboration with IU singing "Nagging."

498
01:01:12,590 --> 01:01:15,820
[A song about nagging lovely to one's lover]

499
01:01:15,820 --> 01:01:18,970
[IU and Seulong's sweet harmony stood out]

500
01:01:18,970 --> 01:01:25,100
[Seulong was strongly recommended by the staff to be in a duet with IU]

501
01:01:25,100 --> 01:01:27,960
[This is his first duet showing off a bright and cheerful voice]

502
01:02:28,880 --> 01:02:34,210
But IU is interested in another 2AM member.

503
01:02:34,210 --> 01:02:36,700
Who is your ideal type if you have to choose?

504
01:02:36,700 --> 01:02:37,970
- Among the four?
 - Yes.

505
01:02:37,970 --> 01:02:45,250
Seulong looked cool when I didn't really meet them that much.

506
01:02:45,250 --> 01:02:47,930
He's tall and like a model.

507
01:02:47,930 --> 01:02:50,980
- His looks are not ordinary.
 - He's really good-looking.

508
01:02:50,980 --> 01:02:56,180
But after working together, Jinwoon looked cool.

509
01:02:56,180 --> 01:02:59,500
- Me?
 - You do it.

510
01:02:59,500 --> 01:03:01,420
- Thank you.
 - Take my place.

511
01:03:01,420 --> 01:03:04,360
Seulong is sulking. What's cool about him?

512
01:03:04,360 --> 01:03:06,040
When he smiles.

513
01:03:07,950 --> 01:03:09,270
- Thank you.
 - When his eyes disappear?

514
01:03:10,090 --> 01:03:12,270
I feel uncomfortable being in the middle.

515
01:03:12,270 --> 01:03:16,310
Jinwoon, did you create another space in your heart?

516
01:03:16,310 --> 01:03:19,660
And Changmin? You lost if you feel jealous.

517
01:03:22,610 --> 01:03:30,720
[Changmin]

518
01:03:30,860 --> 01:03:32,590
Please introduce yourselves.

519
01:03:32,590 --> 01:03:37,110
- I'm Lee Hyun of 8Eight.
 - I'm Changmin of 2AM.

520
01:03:37,110 --> 01:03:41,210
We have to introduce in our project name too.

521
01:03:41,210 --> 01:03:43,670
Hi, we're Homme.

522
01:03:45,260 --> 01:03:47,990
Changmin was part of Homme with Lee Hyun of 8Eight.

523
01:03:47,990 --> 01:03:54,860
Songs with their unique voices were born as they are great vocalists.

524
01:04:03,260 --> 01:04:06,010
[Two great vocalists, Changmin and Lee Hyun, gave birth to...]

525
01:04:06,010 --> 01:04:08,360
[Bang Si-hyuk's first project (Homme by Hitman Bang)]

526
01:04:08,360 --> 01:04:11,700
[This is Homme's first single]

527
01:04:11,700 --> 01:04:13,980
[It's a hybrid rock with a cool guitar and drum sounds]

528
01:04:13,980 --> 01:04:16,270
[The lyrics calmly describe the feeling after breaking up]

529
01:04:16,270 --> 01:04:20,220
[Their uniquely cool voices were memorable]

530
01:04:23,780 --> 01:04:29,770
He gave off a masculine appeal different from when he's in 2AM.

531
01:04:44,160 --> 01:04:48,310
["Man Should Laugh" is the title track of their first mini-album for summer]

532
01:05:08,580 --> 01:05:11,550
[A song mixing American style rock with sweet synthpop]

533
01:05:11,550 --> 01:05:14,320
[This was released for summer like their first single]

534
01:05:14,320 --> 01:05:17,530
[Their voices stand out and make us feel the coolness]

535
01:06:28,220 --> 01:06:36,380
[Jo Kwon]

536
01:06:36,590 --> 01:06:41,510
Jo Kwon released his first solo album in 2012 with a shocking performance.

537
01:06:41,510 --> 01:06:44,470
He showed off his talents.

538
01:06:53,290 --> 01:06:58,030
[His uniquely bright energy can be felt in this electronic dance song]

539
01:06:58,030 --> 01:07:00,380
[Music, appearances, performance, and even the music video]

540
01:07:00,380 --> 01:07:05,980
[Many different things were shown in the title track of his first solo album]

541
01:07:05,980 --> 01:07:12,060
[His own bouncy electronic dance song was made collaborating with artists from abroad]

542
01:07:12,060 --> 01:07:14,970
[The kitsch stage outfits and album jacket utilizing pop art were memorable]

543
01:07:53,700 --> 01:07:59,600
He wore appalling high heels and did a performance only he can do.

544
01:08:10,350 --> 01:08:13,480
[There's a wild feel to this song like the title]

545
01:08:13,480 --> 01:08:16,110
[This song competed with the title track to the end]

546
01:08:16,110 --> 01:08:19,410
[The vocal effect is as if it's echoing from a cave]

547
01:08:19,410 --> 01:08:23,380
[The intense lyrics alluding himself to an animal stood out]

548
01:09:08,950 --> 01:09:12,320
You gave a warning to your members?

549
01:09:12,320 --> 01:09:17,460
It's been 4 years as I was a part of 2AM.

550
01:09:17,460 --> 01:09:21,070
We didn't have any big fights, and if we did, we resolved it.

551
01:09:21,070 --> 01:09:27,480
But I was really hurt by them this time and want to talk about it.

552
01:09:27,480 --> 01:09:28,930
You have to let go of that.

553
01:09:28,930 --> 01:09:33,830
You'll feel light if you do it in public.

554
01:09:33,830 --> 01:09:40,780
I was filming my solo music video for about 3 days without sleep.

555
01:09:40,780 --> 01:09:45,210
When a music video or album jacket is being shot...

556
01:09:45,210 --> 01:09:49,870
Labelmates will sometimes come for support.

557
01:09:49,870 --> 01:09:58,170
The other members come to support when one of them is doing a solo.

558
01:09:58,170 --> 01:10:04,140
My members didn't come on the first day of filming.

559
01:10:04,140 --> 01:10:10,690
On the second day, 2PM's Wooyoung was also filming a music video.

560
01:10:10,690 --> 01:10:15,000
I asked him, "Did your members stop by?"

561
01:10:15,000 --> 01:10:17,700
He said they already came and left.

562
01:10:18,100 --> 01:10:19,740
[Suddenly we're starting to compare them to 2AM!]

563
01:10:20,450 --> 01:10:24,730
I felt sad and went to the restroom to pick my nose...

564
01:10:24,730 --> 01:10:30,240
These black things came out due to the dust and I was welling up with tears.

565
01:10:31,430 --> 01:10:35,350
I don't know why but I felt really sad.

566
01:10:35,350 --> 01:10:40,760
On the last day, filming ended at 9 in the morning.

567
01:10:40,760 --> 01:10:44,410
Seulong texted me, "How's filming?"

568
01:10:44,410 --> 01:10:49,450
I replied, "It's going well," thinking that he's coming.

569
01:10:49,450 --> 01:10:53,270
He replied, "Good luck. I'm tired and going to sleep."

570
01:10:53,270 --> 01:10:55,400
[Oh you poor thing]

571
01:10:56,020 --> 01:11:03,770
I was really sad and didn't even want to send an emoticon.

572
01:11:03,770 --> 01:11:06,690
So I texted "alright" with a tilde.

573
01:11:06,690 --> 01:11:09,250
At first I didn't want to put in the tilde.

574
01:11:09,250 --> 01:11:10,310
You might look timid without it.

575
01:11:10,310 --> 01:11:13,870
There's a difference with and without a tilde.

576
01:11:13,870 --> 01:11:15,810
He might think he's sulking without that tilde.

577
01:11:15,810 --> 01:11:18,970
The feeling is different.

578
01:11:18,970 --> 01:11:25,480
I was really sad and thought this feeling won't go away.

579
01:11:25,480 --> 01:11:30,710
So I sent another text even to Changmin and Jinwoon.

580
01:11:30,710 --> 01:11:36,990
I texted, "Today's the last day of filming. How's everyone?"

581
01:11:36,990 --> 01:11:38,770
That's weird.

582
01:11:38,770 --> 01:11:44,820
"Wooyoung is also filming today and all his members came and left."

583
01:11:44,820 --> 01:11:48,950
- You were straightforward.
 - That was around 5 AM.

584
01:11:48,950 --> 01:11:51,760
Changmin wakes up at that time.

585
01:11:51,760 --> 01:11:56,580
I got 5-6 texts from him.

586
01:11:56,580 --> 01:11:59,740
I felt that they were going to come.

587
01:11:59,740 --> 01:12:02,950
- Like a surprise?
 - A surprise party?

588
01:12:02,950 --> 01:12:07,700
- Something like a hidden camera.
 - They're pretending not to know.

589
01:12:07,700 --> 01:12:10,350
Thinking they will appear from somewhere but where?

590
01:12:10,350 --> 01:12:11,690
That's right.

591
01:12:11,690 --> 01:12:19,170
It felt they will walk out of there or wait in the waiting room.

592
01:12:19,170 --> 01:12:21,810
They didn't come at all.

593
01:12:21,810 --> 01:12:23,100
[Oh my!]

594
01:12:23,100 --> 01:12:24,440
Do they know you're coming on this show?

595
01:12:24,440 --> 01:12:27,760
Yes, but they don't know I'm talking about this.

596
01:12:27,760 --> 01:12:29,040
They don't?

597
01:12:29,040 --> 01:12:31,480
So we prepared...

598
01:12:31,480 --> 01:12:32,750
[Prepared?]

599
01:12:33,110 --> 01:12:37,150
Since this is Jo Kwon's first solo album and variety show appearance...

600
01:12:37,150 --> 01:12:41,290
We have a special corner. Music please!

601
01:12:42,260 --> 01:12:45,740
[I miss you to death]

602
01:12:45,740 --> 01:12:48,040
[Explosive acting!]

603
01:12:53,020 --> 01:12:58,580
Someone is here in the studio.

604
01:13:01,350 --> 01:13:04,440
It's the one you want to see the most. Who is it?

605
01:13:04,440 --> 01:13:05,980
My mom.

606
01:13:07,810 --> 01:13:09,850
[Unexpected answer!]

607
01:13:12,430 --> 01:13:14,200
[Do they call his mom?]

608
01:13:14,550 --> 01:13:16,420
Anyone else?

609
01:13:17,810 --> 01:13:19,490
2AM members!

610
01:13:19,490 --> 01:13:22,250
You want to see them? Shout out to them!

611
01:13:22,250 --> 01:13:24,730
- I miss 2AM!
 - Louder!

612
01:13:24,730 --> 01:13:26,360
I miss you!

613
01:13:34,520 --> 01:13:38,230
[Surprise appearance by 2AM's Jinwoon!]

614
01:13:43,420 --> 01:13:45,250
[The youngest member came in a heartbeat for Jo Kwon!]

615
01:13:46,900 --> 01:13:49,440
Oh my! I'm about to cry!

616
01:13:51,510 --> 01:13:54,250
[He cries as soon as he sees Jinwoon!]

617
01:13:58,870 --> 01:14:00,790
[He's wailing!]

618
01:14:01,740 --> 01:14:04,270
[He was really hurt]

619
01:14:04,270 --> 01:14:06,440
[People might think a separated family reunited...]

620
01:14:06,440 --> 01:14:07,760
[Don't cry!]

621
01:14:07,760 --> 01:14:14,610
Jinwoon appeared for Jo Kwon who was feeling sad. He was touched.

622
01:14:17,630 --> 01:14:25,960
[Jinwoon]

623
01:14:26,050 --> 01:14:33,160
It's known that Jinwoon didn't have any solo activities unlike the other members.

624
01:14:34,090 --> 01:14:38,620
Jo Kwon was busy in sitcoms and variety shows...

625
01:14:38,620 --> 01:14:47,960
Seulong was in a duet with IU, something that I wanted to do.

626
01:14:47,960 --> 01:14:51,460
I even believed in Changmin...

627
01:14:51,460 --> 01:14:53,690
Why is it "even" for me?

628
01:14:54,030 --> 01:15:01,070
It's okay because he was in a duet with Lee Hyun of 8Eight.

629
01:15:01,070 --> 01:15:04,260
I'm the only one without a schedule.

630
01:15:04,260 --> 01:15:08,300
But aren't you the busiest now?

631
01:15:08,300 --> 01:15:09,750
Oh! Now?

632
01:15:11,100 --> 01:15:12,990
Now...

633
01:15:12,990 --> 01:15:14,340
This is about you!

634
01:15:14,340 --> 01:15:17,530
[The one with the "top star" disease is Jinwoon?]

635
01:15:20,540 --> 01:15:22,650
It's actually about me.

636
01:15:22,650 --> 01:15:25,840
[The one with the "top star" disease is Jinwoon!]

637
01:15:25,840 --> 01:15:31,740
I started off with a solo album releasing first and second albums.

638
01:15:31,740 --> 01:15:38,200
I played the lead in "Dream High 2."

639
01:15:38,200 --> 01:15:41,570
When I released my first solo album...

640
01:15:41,570 --> 01:15:49,390
Many band members and musicians heard it and told me I was great.

641
01:15:49,850 --> 01:15:56,640
He's a former rock band member and went solo at a Rock festival in 2011.

642
01:16:41,060 --> 01:16:46,230
He's finally on his long-awaited dream stage. This suits him as well.

643
01:16:49,420 --> 01:16:57,520
He's doing his part on "Law of the Jungle" with unique vigor and quick adaptability.

644
01:16:57,520 --> 01:16:59,910
[Will he make physical contact today?]

645
01:17:01,670 --> 01:17:02,930
[Come here]

646
01:17:06,670 --> 01:17:10,500
[What is he doing?]

647
01:17:10,500 --> 01:17:12,810
[He's trying to lure them by becoming a tall tree]

648
01:17:18,460 --> 01:17:21,070
[Jinwoon lures them with a familiar sound]

649
01:17:22,700 --> 01:17:24,770
[It climbed!]

650
01:17:25,930 --> 01:17:28,750
[Lemurs are known to be sociable]

651
01:17:28,750 --> 01:17:32,770
[Maybe since it's the second day, it became close to them]

652
01:17:34,860 --> 01:17:36,650
[Awesome!]

653
01:17:39,880 --> 01:17:41,180
[Made physical contact!]

654
01:17:42,110 --> 01:17:45,020
[A concert on the spot for finding water?]

655
01:17:45,020 --> 01:17:48,080
[How do I dig you?]

656
01:17:49,320 --> 01:17:52,670
[If you dig me and try to dig...]

657
01:17:52,670 --> 01:17:56,500
[Bring a shovel and dig]

658
01:17:56,500 --> 01:17:59,160
[To not make this tiring...]

659
01:17:59,160 --> 01:18:02,900
[To be able to take this water...]

660
01:18:02,900 --> 01:18:06,080
[If it doesn't work, we can't take it]

661
01:18:06,080 --> 01:18:09,240
[Even though I die, I can't dig it]

662
01:18:09,240 --> 01:18:10,760
[He wrote his own song about his crush!]

663
01:18:10,760 --> 01:18:15,280
I tried to hide her from my head and heart...

664
01:18:15,280 --> 01:18:19,940
But I can't because she's so bright.

665
01:18:21,000 --> 01:18:24,490
[You're So Bright
 - Jeong Jinwoon]

666
01:18:24,490 --> 01:18:31,030
[You're so bright]

667
01:18:31,030 --> 01:18:40,040
[I hide under a shade that will block you]

668
01:18:42,100 --> 01:18:45,950
[These two are absorbed]

669
01:18:45,950 --> 01:18:50,660
[In his sweet voice]

670
01:18:52,230 --> 01:18:55,990
[A sad song on unrequited love]

671
01:18:55,990 --> 01:19:00,440
[In the middle of the desert]

672
01:19:05,910 --> 01:19:10,080
[I draw you this time]

673
01:19:10,080 --> 01:19:12,860
[Jeong Jinwoon the jungle's wandering minstrel]

674
01:19:13,250 --> 01:19:16,690
That was really good!

675
01:19:16,690 --> 01:19:19,470
Don't fall in love with me.

676
01:19:21,120 --> 01:19:22,370
[Don't worry about that]

677
01:19:22,750 --> 01:19:24,720
I should leave.

678
01:19:25,840 --> 01:19:28,300
[Jung-chul feels left out]

679
01:19:35,010 --> 01:19:39,800
They return in 2012 after a year and a half.

680
01:19:39,800 --> 01:19:46,600
The quintessence of their ballad was felt again with a matured sentiment and voice.

681
01:20:11,670 --> 01:20:18,580
[The calm piano and cello melody goes with their profound timbre]

682
01:20:18,580 --> 01:20:23,690
[They convey a man's empty feeling after a breakup in a calm, heartrending voice]

683
01:20:23,690 --> 01:20:29,620
[Its release was postponed 3 times for completion, but an LP was also made]

684
01:20:29,620 --> 01:20:33,130
[This title track is nostalgic and worth possessing]

685
01:21:08,390 --> 01:21:14,150
It'll be great if we could listen to more of 2AM's songs in the future.

686
01:23:06,520 --> 01:23:14,760
[A soft piano melody and strings go well with their subtle timbre]

687
01:23:14,760 --> 01:23:18,950
[Their voices are calm as if having a soliloquy]

688
01:23:18,950 --> 01:23:23,070
[The plaintiveness is expressed dramatically as the melody gradually builds up]

689
01:23:23,070 --> 01:23:27,220
[It was tough in the beginning due to the song's high level of difficulty]

690
01:23:27,220 --> 01:23:31,340
[But they picked this as the title track after listening to the guide]

